Synopsis: The director of How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days and Miss Congeniality cooks up a sizzling comedy about two lifelong pals (Hayden Christensen and Emma Roberts) whose romance is threatened by their families’ rival. Aaspiring chef, Nikki, returns to her hometown Toronto neighbourhood while she waits for a work visa to come through. Almost immediately, she runs into childhood pal Leo, who she’s been estranged from since their parents opened rival pizza restaurants. Their parents’ feud escalates even further when Leo and Nikki’s longtime friendship blossoms into romance.  Starring: Emma Roberts, Hayden Christensen, Alyssa Milano, Andrew Phung, Andrea Martin and Jane Seymour  Directed by: Donald Petrie     